%I A394669 #24 Mar 28 2026 09:45:49
%S A394669 1,1,1,1,1,2,2,1,1,1,1,2,1,1
%N A394669 Number of terms in the discriminant of the monic polynomial f(x) = x^n + a1 * x^{n-1} + ... + an whose absolute coefficient is equal to A240582(n).
%H A394669 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="https://github.com/manman4/OEIS_03/blob/main/394/394669/394669_01.c">C program</a> (github)
%e A394669 For n=6, f(x) = x^6 + a1 * x^5 + a2 * x^4 + ... + a6. The maximum absolute coefficient is A240582(6) = 77760. There are a(6) = 2 such terms:
%e A394669   -77760 * a3 * a4 * a5 * a6^3 (vector: [0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 3])
%e A394669   -77760 * a1 * a2 * a3 * a6^4 (vector: [1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 4])
%e A394669 Both have total weight 3*1 + 4*1 + 5*1 + 6*3 = 1*1 + 2*1 + 3*1 + 6*4 = 30 = 6 * 5.
%e A394669 .
%e A394669 Term with the largest absolute coefficient
%e A394669   n  | Monomial
